Name: Lynn Burton
About:
Blue Pearl Enterprise is a globally-minded corporation in word and deed. We see business as means to realize our goal of preserving the environment for future generations. Even our name is derived from the Earth itself which from space, has the appearance of a beautiful blue pearl.

Comprising nearly 71 percent of the Earth's surface and containing 97 percent of the planet's water, our ocean and lakes play an integral role in various ecosystems including climate and weather. The ocean supports the life of nearly 50 percent of all species on Earth and helps sustain that life by providing 20 percent of the animal protein and five percent of the total protein in the human diet.

Sadly, humanity has begun to impact the ocean ecosystems in what could soon become an irreversible manner. Thousands of tons of non-biodegradable waste are turning our oceans into a toxic mess. Sealife is being affected and some species face the possibility of extinction. It is with these realities in mind that Blue Pearl Enterprise has resolved to make every effort possible to reverse this process and restore the world's oceans to their former health.

Enlisting the aid of major global corporations and experts in both the private and public sector, we intend to find solutions to bring this major undertaking to fruition. You can help us in this process through several avenues. A percentage of all Blue Pearl Enterprise sales is donated to the Blue Pearl Project North Pacific Gyre clean up. Together we can make a difference!
